1- Provide limited green fodder, concentrate feed, Compound feed. Do not provide Cold and hot water. 
2-After placenta discharge provide Lukewarm water for drink, this practice follow next 2-3 day. 
3- Protection from cold or hot wind and extremes temperature. 
4- Feeding a Lukewarm crude sugar mixed with bran mash 
5- Milked first time, milker must ensure that all blockages from teats removed. 
6- Succulent green, palatable fodders containing 50-60% legumes are suitable while amount concentrates should be increased gradually in three weeks.
